sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id)
FROM predictions
WHERE model_id = 1 AND status = 'completed';

SELECT dataset_name, data_type
FROM datasets
WHERE dataset_id = (SELECT dataset_id FROM models WHERE model_id = 1);

external_knowledge:
- 'mastermind' refers to the user who made the most recent prediction; 
- 'latest forecast' refers to the most recent prediction made using the latest model; 
- 'most cutting-edge model' refers to the most recently trained model; 
- 'freshest data' refers to the most recent dataset.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM model_versions
WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE username = 'bob_williams');

SELECT user_id
FROM models
WHERE accuracy = (SELECT MAX(accuracy) FROM models);

SELECT version_number
FROM model_versions
WHERE update_date = (SELECT MAX(update_date) FROM model_versions);
